OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCut VAT in Queen's Speech, 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FLiberal Democrats urge     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fministers                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Liberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey   
OL,6, has demanded an "emergency" tax cut in 
OL,7, next week's Queen's Speech.            
OL,9,FHe told the BBC that bringing VAT down 
OL,10,Ffrom 20% to 17.5% as soon as possible  
OL,11,Fwould help reduce inflation, which has 
OL,12,Frisen sharply in recent months.        
OL,14,FSir Ed added that he was "really       
OL,15,Fannoyed", saying the Conservatives had 
OL,16,F"no plans" to assist households.       
OL,18,FBut Business Secretary Kwasi Kwarteng  
OL,19,Fsaid the government was giving         
OL,20,Fhouseholds "substantial help".         
